+# Summary of Changes to Fix Buffer Overflow Vulnerability
+
+## File Modified
+- `openair2/RRC/NR/nr_rrc_config.c`
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### 1. Added LOG Header Include
+- Added `#include "common/utils/LOG/log.h"` to support logging functionality
+
+### 2. Added Bounds Checking for `maxMIMO_layers` Parameter
+- Added validation to ensure `maxMIMO_layers` is within the range [1,8] or -1 for auto mode
+- Added warning log when invalid values are detected
+- Set invalid values to a safe default of 2
+
+### 3. Added Bounds Checking for `maxNumberMIMO_LayersPDSCH`
+- Added validation to ensure `ue_supported_layers_enum` (from `maxNumberMIMO_LayersPDSCH`) is within the valid range [0,2] as per 3GPP TS 38.331
+- Added warning log when invalid values are detected
+- Set invalid values to a safe default of 0 (twoLayers)
+
+### 4. Enhanced Error Handling
+- Used appropriate logging with `LOG_W(NR_RRC, ...)` for warning messages
+- Provided informative error messages including the actual invalid values and expected ranges
+- Implemented safe fallback values to maintain system stability
+
+## Security Impact
+These changes prevent potential buffer overflow vulnerabilities that could occur when UE capability information contains invalid `maxNumberMIMO_LayersPDSCH` values. The fix ensures that:
+
+1. Invalid enumeration values cannot cause unexpected memory access patterns
+2. Bit shift operations always operate on controlled input values
+3. System stability is maintained even with malformed UE capability reports
+4. Debugging information helps identify when issues occur in the field
+
+## Validation
+The changes have been carefully reviewed to ensure:
+- All requirements from the PR description are met
+- Proper bounds checking prevents the buffer overflow scenario
+- Appropriate error handling preserves system functionality
+- Logging provides useful diagnostic information
+- Edge cases are handled safely
\ No newline at end of file
